dreht sich um die Überlagerung und Mischung von Räumen und Strukturen, um städtische Texturen und ihre architektonischen Eigenschaften und Qualitäten: um die Stadt der radikalen Durchmischung.  aSome time ago, Walter Benjamin and Asja Lacis used the term "porosity" with reference to Naples’ urban characteristics – spaces merging into each other and providing the backdrop for the unforeseen – improvisation as a way of life. Today, the term "porosity" in this context is increasingly used conceptually. Well-known authors from the worlds of architecture, town planning, and landscape design embark on a search for new concepts for a life-enhancing, user-friendly city – with reference to this enigmatic term. The term refers to the overlaying and interweaving of spaces and structures, to urban textures and their architectural properties and qualities – to cities with radically mixed urban functions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCity planning. 4aArchitektur. 4aStadt. 4aStadtplanung. 4aStädtebau. 4aUrbanismus. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aArchitecture.  aCity planning.  aUrban planning.  aUrbanism.1 aAngélil, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAquilar, Giorgia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBates, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeesley, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandis, Nikolai Frhr. von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBru, Eduard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchert, Margitta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab